verses.text_plain: When Israel was a child, then I loved him, and called my son out of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 1When Israel was a child, then I loved him, and called my son out of Egypt.

verses.text_plain: As they called them, so they went from them: they sacrificed unto Baalim, and burned incense to graven images.
verses.verse_html: 2As they called them, so they went from them: they sacrificed unto Baalim, and burned incense to graven images.

verses.text_plain: I taught Ephraim also to go, taking them by their arms; but they knew not that I healed them.
verses.verse_html: 3I taught Ephraim also to go, taking them by their arms; but they knew not that I healed them.

verses.text_plain: I drew them with cords of a man, with bands of love: and I was to them as they that take off the yoke on their jaws, and I laid meat unto them.
verses.verse_html:
4I drew them with cords of a man, with bands of love: and I was to them as they that take off the yoke on their jaws, and I laid meat unto them. ▼
▼ take off: Heb. lift up

tokens.text: and I was to them as they that take off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ take off: Heb. lift up

verses.text_plain: He shall not return into the land of Egypt, but the Assyrian shall be his king, because they refused to return.
verses.verse_html: 5He shall not return into the land of Egypt, but the Assyrian shall be his king, because they refused to return.

verses.text_plain: And the sword shall abide on his cities, and shall consume his branches, and devour them, because of their own counsels.
verses.verse_html: 6And the sword shall abide on his cities, and shall consume his branches, and devour them, because of their own counsels.

verses.text_plain: And my people are bent to backsliding from me: though they called them to the most High, none at all would exalt him.
verses.verse_html:
7And my people are bent to backsliding from me: though they called them to the most High, none at all would exalt him. ▼
▼ none…: Heb. together they exalted not

footnotes.body_text: ▼ none…: Heb. together they exalted not
footnotes.body_html: ▼ none…: Heb. together they exalted not

verses.text_plain: How shall I give thee up, Ephraim? how shall I deliver thee, Israel? how shall I make thee as Admah? how shall I set thee as Zeboim? mine heart is turned within me, my repentings are kindled together.
verses.verse_html: 8How shall I give thee up, Ephraim? how shall I deliver thee, Israel? how shall I make thee as Admah? how shall I set thee as Zeboim? mine heart is turned within me, my repentings are kindled together.

tokens.text: How shall I give thee up

verses.text_plain: I will not execute the fierceness of mine anger, I will not return to destroy Ephraim: for I am God, and not man; the Holy One in the midst of thee: and I will not enter into the city.
verses.verse_html: 9I will not execute the fierceness of mine anger, I will not return to destroy Ephraim: for I am God, and not man; the Holy One in the midst of thee: and I will not enter into the city.

tokens.text: of thee: and I will not enter

verses.text_plain: They shall walk after the Lord: he shall roar like a lion: when he shall roar, then the children shall tremble from the west.
verses.verse_html: 10They shall walk after the Lord: he shall roar like a lion: when he shall roar, then the children shall tremble from the west.

verses.text_plain: They shall tremble as a bird out of Egypt, and as a dove out of the land of Assyria: and I will place them in their houses, saith the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 11They shall tremble as a bird out of Egypt, and as a dove out of the land of Assyria: and I will place them in their houses, saith the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Ephraim compasseth me about with lies, and the house of Israel with deceit: but Judah yet ruleth with God, and is faithful with the saints.
verses.verse_html:
12Ephraim compasseth me about with lies, and the house of Israel with deceit: but Judah yet ruleth with God, and is faithful with the saints. ▼
▼ saints: or, most holy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ saints: or, most holy
